snippet.title: Vexento & HiTydes - Staring At The Lights
snippet.description:
AVAILABLE ON SPOTIFY! - https://open.spotify.com/album/6cfV1FmCejuvTVyphbtste

Heeeey!❤️

This is the last track of The Silent Miracle. There was only supposed to be 7 tracks in this album, but then Jamie (HiTydes) contacted me and shared his brilliant idea with me. (Staring At The Lights with vocals) And i loved it, so i quickly started working on the track from scratch again, to make it fit his vocals as much as possible. and Tadaa.. The 8th track was born! I think it sounds pretty damn chill! :D
(It also fits really well considering the fact that Staring At The Lights was the very first track of the album.)

So now that the whole album is out.. what happens next? Well first of all, all the tracks from The Silent Miracle will soon be available on Spotify and other digital stores for those who are interested in that! And then i'll get back to making more music! I already have a very exciting single coming up sometime soon as well! :)

Check out HiTydes right here:
Twitter: https://twitter.com/HiTydesOfficial
Soundcloud: https://soundcloud.com/hitydes
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/HiTydes/

snippet.description:

www.twitter.com/lessismore9912
www.instagram.com/lessismore9912

How to play:
Standard Tuning - No Capo
F#m, D, A (two measures)
With Capo on 2nd Fret
Em, C, G (two measures)

We play it with the capo because we preferred those chords, but we know not everyone has one or uses one! Hope this helps!

Caroline Shumate and Greg Graves were both born and raised in Houston, TX. They met in high school when they were each chosen to play in YouTube all-star, Tyler Ward's band. They toured nationally with Tyler and discovered how well they played together. With Greg’s infectious beats and Caroline’s mesmerizing guitar and vocal skills they created a striking duo, “The Queen and King.”
